          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Peele's second feature, seen at the South by Southwest premiere. They work through the tethered mythology, Red's 'we're Americans' speech, the swap twist, and the loose logic (the rabbits, the scissors, what happens when a tethered person leaves the country). Lupita Nyong'o's dual performance is the best thing in it; Winston Duke plays the dad for laughs, and Elisabeth Moss and Tim Heidecker turn up as the doomed vacation family partway through."
